gnGenStandardOrg.name: gnGenStandardOrg
gnGenStandardOrg.description: This parameter specifies which international standard is used.

gnGenTxFreqRange.name: gnGenTxFreqRange
gnGenTxFreqRange.description: This parameter specifies frequency ranges in Hertz. Value 1 to 13 are used when the link is working with channels. The notUsed value is used when the link is working with frequency.

gnGenRemoteConnection.name: gnGenRemoteConnection
gnGenRemoteConnection.description: Is the connection between the local manager and the remote manager.

gnGenRemoteDistance.name: gnGenRemoteDistance
gnGenRemoteDistance.description: This field is the distance between the local and remote ODU, in meters. This attribute does not auto-detect the distance. It is used as part of the unfaded RSL calculation feature in the element manager.

gnGenInterLenLocalRemote.name: gnGenInterLenLocalRemote
gnGenInterLenLocalRemote.description: This field is the FEC interleaver length - DONT CHANGE THIS FIELD !!!. WRITE will change both local and remote sides.

gnGenTxFreqLocalRemote.name: gnGenTxFreqLocalRemote
gnGenTxFreqLocalRemote.description: This parameter indicates the radio TX channel number. WRITE will change both LOCAL and REMOTE sides. Not all radios will support TX frequency change via channel numbers.

gnGenRealTimeandDate.name: gnGenRealTimeandDate
gnGenRealTimeandDate.description: This parameter specifies the real time and date Format 'YYYY-MM-DD,HH:MM:SS' (Hexadecimal). A date-time specification. field octets contents range ----- ------ -------- ----- 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) 7 8 deci-seconds 0..9 8 9 direction from UTC '+' / '-' 9 10 hours from UTC 0..11 10 11 minutes from UTC 0..59 For example, Tuesday May 26, 1992 at 1:30:15 PM EDT would be displayed as: 07 c8 05 1a 0d 1e 0f 00 ( 1992 -5 -26,13:30:15 ) Note that if only local time is known, then timezone information (fields 8-10) is not present.

gnGenCfgDeviceTable.name: gnGenCfgDeviceTable
gnGenCfgDeviceTable.description: This table contains general configuration info per device, local and remote.

gnGenCfgDeviceEntry.name: gnGenCfgDeviceEntry
gnGenCfgDeviceEntry.description: Entry containing general configuration information, for both local and remote sides.

gnGenCfgDeviceId.name: gnGenCfgDeviceId
gnGenCfgDeviceId.description: This value indicates the device table entry (local or Remote).

gnGenCfgDeviceOperation.name: gnGenCfgDeviceOperation
gnGenCfgDeviceOperation.description: This parameter allows the NMS to perform operations. (3) will implement software RESET (4) will SET all factory default configurations, including IP address! (5) will CLEAR IDU software NOTE: CLEARING IDU software will cause the IDU to use the factory BOOT software version. 4 and 5 will take place only after reset of the IDU

gnGenCfgActivateLoopback.name: gnGenCfgActivateLoopback
gnGenCfgActivateLoopback.description: This parameter controls the loop back diagnostics operations. For remote units, only SPI, MUX and MDM loopbacks are allowed.

gnGenCfgF1DataChanConnector.name: gnGenCfgF1DataChanConnector
gnGenCfgF1DataChanConnector.description: This is the physical interface of the F1 line data channel (USER CHANNEL connection).

gnGenCfgWaySideConnector.name: gnGenCfgWaySideConnector
gnGenCfgWaySideConnector.description: This is the physical interface of the radio E1 way side channel (WAYSIDE CHANNEL connection).

gnGenCfgActivateChanLoopback.name: gnGenCfgActivateChanLoopback
gnGenCfgActivateChanLoopback.description: This parameter controls the USER CHANNEL and WAYSIDE channel loopback diagnostic operations. (3) will activate the 64k data channel loopback (USER CHANNEL) (4) will activate the WAYSIDE CHANNEL loopback.

gnGenCfgInterLenLocalOnly.name: gnGenCfgInterLenLocalOnly
gnGenCfgInterLenLocalOnly.description: This field is the FEC interleaver length .DONT CAHNGE THIS FIELD !!! . WRITE will change the local side only.

gnGenCfgSlipIp.name: gnGenCfgSlipIp
gnGenCfgSlipIp.description: This is the SERIAL interface IP address. Included for future development, not currently supported.

gnGenCfgSlipModemConnection.name: gnGenCfgSlipModemConnection
gnGenCfgSlipModemConnection.description: The telephone number to which the modem will initialize a call, upon generation of a TRAP. The number must be entered numerically (for example 18001234567).

gnGenCfgAlarmSeverity.name: gnGenCfgAlarmSeverity
gnGenCfgAlarmSeverity.description: This field is used only by the element management application Every Trap severity 4 bits. 15 (MAJOR), 7 (MINOR), 3 (WARNING) and 1 (EVENT) options. The first 4 bits ODU Power supply severity, then the Synthesizer severity ,then Tx level then RX level ODU temperature, ODU loopback , IDU power supply , Cable, Modem, IDU temperature, IDU loopbacks, External Alarm 1, External Alarm 2 ,External Alarm 3, External Alarm 4, External Alarm 5, External Alarm 6, External Alarm 7, External Alarm 8, Remote connectivity, LOF, LOS, EXC, SD J0 mismatch and system fault.

gnGenCfgODUSerialNumber.name: gnGenCfgODUSerialNumber
gnGenCfgODUSerialNumber.description: This is the ODU serial number - up to 20 characters

gnGenCfgIDUSerialNumber.name: gnGenCfgIDUSerialNumber
gnGenCfgIDUSerialNumber.description: This is the IDU serial number - up to 20 characters

gnGenCfgAlarmText.name: gnGenCfgAlarmText
gnGenCfgAlarmText.description: The private trap text, describing the last generated trap text.

gnGenCfgTrapSeverity.name: gnGenCfgTrapSeverity
gnGenCfgTrapSeverity.description: The current Trap severity, describing the last generated trap severity

gnGenCfgLeftMediumConnector.name: gnGenCfgLeftMediumConnector
gnGenCfgLeftMediumConnector.description: For ACCESS hardware, this indicates the first (left) interface connector.

gnGenCfgMiddleMediumConnector.name: gnGenCfgMiddleMediumConnector
gnGenCfgMiddleMediumConnector.description: For ACCESS hardware, this indicates the second (right)interface connector.

gnGenCfgPrimaryClockSource.name: gnGenCfgPrimaryClockSource
gnGenCfgPrimaryClockSource.description: The primary clock source, configurable for ACCESS radios only.

gnGenCfgSecondaryClockSource.name: gnGenCfgSecondaryClockSource

gnGenCfgTrapOption.name: gnGenCfgTrapOption
gnGenCfgTrapOption.description: This item defines various trap options (0-31): 0 - SNSN (STANDARD TRAPS DO NOT INCLUDE SERIAL NUMBER) 1 - ASN (ALL TRAPS INCLUDE SERIAL NUMBER) 2 - SNSN, DNLR (DO NOT REPORT LOCAL TRAPS FROM REMOTE IDU) 3 - ASN, DNLR 4 - SNSN, EVT (USE DIFFERENT TRAP ID FOR EACH ALARM TYPE) 5 - ASN, EVT 6 - SNSN, DNLR, EVT 7 - ASN, DNLR, EVT * - Add 8 to your choice for excluding traps with id >= 128. Example: for SNSN, DNLR with this filter write 10 (=8+2). ** - Add another 16 to your choice in order to send 'clear' traps with zero severity.

gnGenCfgClearLoopTimeout.name: gnGenCfgClearLoopTimeout

gnGenStatDeviceId.description: This value indicates which device is involved in the specific row.

gnGenStatDeviceCelsiusTemp.name: gnGenStatDeviceCelsiusTemp
gnGenStatDeviceCelsiusTemp.description: This is the temperature of the modem of the IDU in degrees of Celsius.

gnGenStatDeviceFahrenheitTemp.name: gnGenStatDeviceFahrenheitTemp
gnGenStatDeviceFahrenheitTemp.description: This is the temperature of the modem of the IDU in degrees of Fahrenheit.

gnGenStatDevicePowerSupply.name: gnGenStatDevicePowerSupply
gnGenStatDevicePowerSupply.description: This octet represents the status of the power supplies of the IDU: bit 1 on = 3.3V faulty bit 2 on = -5V faulty bit 3 on = 5V faulty. bit 4 on = +8V faulty

gnGenStatDeviceCable.name: gnGenStatDeviceCable
gnGenStatDeviceCable.description: Status of the cable to the ODU.

gnGenStatDeviceDryContact.name: gnGenStatDeviceDryContact

The MSB represents external alarm 8. For example when only external alarm 1 is on the status value will be 0xFE00

gnGenStatDeviceLeds.name: gnGenStatDeviceLeds

gnGenStatInternalCommunication.name: gnGenStatInternalCommunication

gnGenStatDeviceFanStatus.name: gnGenStatDeviceFanStatus

gnGenStatDeviceODUStatus.name: gnGenStatDeviceODUStatus
gnGenStatDeviceODUStatus.description: ODU status reported with this parameter. Bit1 is MSB. The bit is set when a fault occurs. The bit is cleared when the fault clears. bit 1 = Power Supply status bit 2 = Synthesizer lock status bit 3 = Tx level status bit 4 = ATPC status bit 5 = Rx level status bit 6 = Not currently used. bit 7 = Temperature status bit 8 = Not currently used. bit 9 = ODU loopback status. bit 10 = Internal use (by application). bit 11 = Tx is in Mute.

gnGenStatDeviceIDUStatus.name: gnGenStatDeviceIDUStatus

gnGenStatDeviceRSTStatus.name: gnGenStatDeviceRSTStatus
gnGenStatDeviceRSTStatus.description: The bit is set when a fault occurs. The bit is cleared when the fault clears. bit 1 = Line loss of frame status bit 2 = Radio loss of frame status bit 3 = Line EXC status bit 4 = Radio EXC status bit 5 = Line SD status bit 6 = Radio SD status bit 7 = loss of signal status bit 8 = J0 mismatch. bit 9 = Line UNE status.

gnGenTxFreqNumLocalRemote.name: gnGenTxFreqNumLocalRemote

gnGenFeatureSupport.name: gnGenFeatureSupport
gnGenFeatureSupport.description: Inidcation for feature support. msb is for bit #1. The bit is set when a specific feature is support. Bit #1 - Tftp server support. Bit #2 - Cold reset support. Bit #3 - Severity critical for external alarm. Bit #4 - MRMC filter table. Bit #5 - NeighborIP Support Fast and DS3. Bit #6 - Auxiliary channel drawer routing support. Bit #7 - Single drawer external protection support. Bit #8 - dual drawer external protection not support. Bit #9 - Left Drawer XPIC hardware support (0 - support, 1 - not support). Bit #10 - Right Drawer XPIC hardware support (0 - support, 1 - not support). Bit #11 - Internal Protection Not Supported (0 - support, 1 - not support). Bit #12 - One Ws Channel Only (0 - FALSE, 1 - TRUE). Bit #13 - Protect option not support (0 - support, 1 - not support). Bit #14 - UC ethernet support (0 - not support, 1 - support). Bit #15 - WSC only disable (0 - enable & disable, 1 - only disable). Bit #16 - UC only disable (0 - enable & disable, 1 - only disable). Bit #17 - EOW only disable (0 - enable & disable, 1 - only disable). Bit #18 - Left Drawer modem latency Not support (0 - support, 1 - not support). Bit #19 - Right Drawer modem latency Not support (0 - support, 1 - not support). Bit #20 - Clear PM for drawer (0 - support, 1 - not support). Bit #21 - Allow Sync mode in UC#2 (0 - not allow, 1 - allow). Bit #22 - External Alarm Switch not support (0 - support, 1 - not support). Bit #23 - Is Hitless config [Divesity Type,Revertive Mode and Revertive Time] are disable (0 - enable, 1 - disable). Bit #24 - QoS left carrier support (1 - support, 0 - not support). Bit #25 - QoS right carrier support (1 - support, 0 - not support). Bit #26 - ACM left carrier support (1 - support, 0 - not support). Bit #27 - ACM right carrier support (1 - support, 0 - not support). Bit #28 - ACM adaptive left carrier support (1 - support, 0 - not support). Bit #29 - ACM adaptive right carrier support (1 - support, 0 - not support). Bit #30 - Single left board reset not support (0 - support, 1 - not support). Bit #31 - Single right board reset not support (0 - support, 1 - not support). Bit #32 - Left drawer reset not support (0 - support,1 - not support). Bit #33 - Right drawer reset not support (0 - support,1 - not support). Bit #34 - All drawers reset support (0 - not support,1 - support). Bit #35 - License manager not support (0 - support,1 - not support). Bit #36 - Multi radio protection support (1 - support,0 - not support). Bit #37 - Copy IDC to left drawer not support (0 - support,1 - not support). Bit #38 - Copy IDC to right drawer not support (0 - support,1 - not support). Bit #39 - Copy IDC to all drawers support (0 - not support,1 - support). Bit #40 - Gigabit flow control support on left carrier(1 - support,0 - not support). Bit #41 - Gigabit flow control support on right carrier(1 - support,0 - not support). Bit #42 - Gigabit PM and statistics support on left carrier(1 - support,0 - not support). Bit #42 - Gigabit PM and statistics support on right carrier(1 - support,0 - not support).

gnAgnMgrIP.description: This value indicates the managers IP address. WRITE an IP address of all zeroes (0.0.0.0) will remove the entry.

gnAgnMgrAlarmGroupMask.name: gnAgnMgrAlarmGroupMask
gnAgnMgrAlarmGroupMask.description: bit mask .1 is 'send a trap' 0 is 'dont send a trap'. The list of alarms from MSB to LSB is: bit 1 = Power Supply Alarm bit 2 = Cable Alarm bit 3 = Temperature Alarm bit 4 = External Alarm bit 5 = Radio Alarm bit 6 = Modem Alarm bit 7 = Line Alarm bit 8 = SDH Alarm bit 9 = BER Alarm bit 10 = System fault Alarm bit 11 = Maintenance Alarm If this field is 0, only standard traps will be sent to the manager

gnAgnMgrSeverityFilter.name: gnAgnMgrSeverityFilter
gnAgnMgrSeverityFilter.description: This is a bit mask value for masking traps according to its severity. There is a bit for each severity. If the relevant bit is on (1), then the Agent will send traps with this severity, and it won't send if the bit is off (0). The list of bits from LSB to MSB: bit 1 (LSB) = Event. bit 2 = Warning. bit 3 = Minor. bit 4 = Major. bit 5 (MSB) = Critical.

gnAgnLogFileValidEntries.description: This is the number of valid entries in the current logfile. If the management station is not active, the MIB will display up to 100 recent logfile events

gnAgnLogFileValid.name: gnAgnLogFileValid
gnAgnLogFileValid.description: This value indicates the validity of the indexed alarm logfile entry. a VALID log entry is (2) and an INVALID entry is (3).

gnAgnLogFileDate.name: gnAgnLogFileDate
gnAgnLogFileDate.description: This field is the date the alarm occurred, formatted as YYYY-MM-DD. YYYY represents the year, MM the month and DD -the day.

gnAgnLogFileTime.name: gnAgnLogFileTime
gnAgnLogFileTime.description: This field is the hour the alarm occurred - format HH:MM. HH - Hour, MM - minute

gnAgnLogFileSeverity.name: gnAgnLogFileSeverity
gnAgnLogFileSeverity.description: This value indicates the severity of the alarm, 31 for CRITICAL, 15 for MAJOR, 7 for MINOR, 3 for WARNING and 1 for EVENT.

gnAgnLogFileText.name: gnAgnLogFileText
gnAgnLogFileText.description: This field describes the alarm that occurred. Max length 40 characters.

gnAgnLogFileDeviceCelsiusTemp.name: gnAgnLogFileDeviceCelsiusTemp
gnAgnLogFileDeviceCelsiusTemp.description: This is the temperature of the IDU in degrees Celsius, during the alarm acceptance.

gnAgnLogFileDevicePowerSupply.name: gnAgnLogFileDevicePowerSupply
gnAgnLogFileDevicePowerSupply.description: This is the Power supply status of the IDU, during the alarm acceptance bit 1 on = 3.3V faulty bit 2 on = -5V faulty bit 3 on = 5V faulty. bit 4 on = +8V faulty

gnAgnLogFileInternalCommunication.name: gnAgnLogFileInternalCommunication
gnAgnLogFileInternalCommunication.description: This is the internal communication status of the IDU, during the alarm acceptance bit 1 = 1: between main CPU and ODU CPU. bit 2 = 1: between main CPU and MUX CPU. bit 3 = 1: between master main CPU and slave main CPU.

gnAgnLogFileDeviceFanStatus.name: gnAgnLogFileDeviceFanStatus
gnAgnLogFileDeviceFanStatus.description: This is the Fan status of the IDU, during the alarm acceptance bit 1 = Fan1 is faulty. bit 2 = Fan 2 is faulty.

gnAgnLogFileDeviceODUStatus.name: gnAgnLogFileDeviceODUStatus
gnAgnLogFileDeviceODUStatus.description: This is the ODU status during the alarm acceptance bit 1 MSB bit 1 = Power Supply status bit 2 = Synthesizer lock status bit 3 = Tx level status bit 4 = ATPC status bit 5 = Rx level status bit 6 = Not currently used bit 7 = Temperature status bit 8 = Not currently used. bit 9 = Not currently used

gnAgnLogFileDeviceIDUStatus.name: gnAgnLogFileDeviceIDUStatus
gnAgnLogFileDeviceIDUStatus.description: This is the IDU status during the alarm acceptance bit 1 MSB bit 1 = Power status - bit 2 = Cable open status - bit 3 = Cable short status - bit 4 = Modem Lock status bit 5 = Temperature status bit 6 = Not currently used. bit 7 = loopback status bit 8 = External alarm 1 status bit 9 = External alarm 2 status bit 10 = External alarm 3 status bit 11 = External alarm 4 status bit 12 = External alarm 5 status bit 13 = External alarm 6 status bit 14 = External alarm 7 status bit 15 = External alarm 8 status bit 16 = Remote connectivity status. bit 17 = Inner communication status.

gnAgnLogFileOduCelsiusTemp.name: gnAgnLogFileOduCelsiusTemp
gnAgnLogFileOduCelsiusTemp.description: This is the temperature of the ODU in degrees Celsius, during the alarm acceptance.

gnAgnLogFileOduReceiveLevel.name: gnAgnLogFileOduReceiveLevel
gnAgnLogFileOduReceiveLevel.description: This is the received signal level in DBM, during the alarm acceptance

gnAgnLogFileOduSynthesizerVCOLock.name: gnAgnLogFileOduSynthesizerVCOLock
gnAgnLogFileOduSynthesizerVCOLock.description: This is the Synthesizer status, during the alarm acceptance bit 1 on = TX IF synthesizer fault bit 2 on = RX IF synthesizer fault bit 3 on = Xband synthesizer fault bit 4 on = History TX IF synthesizer fault bit 5 on = History RX IF synthesizer fault bit 6 on = History Xband synthesizer fault

gnAgnLogFileOduPowerSupply.name: gnAgnLogFileOduPowerSupply
gnAgnLogFileOduPowerSupply.description: This is the ODU power supply status, during the alarm acceptance bit 1 on = +5V faulty bit 2 on = +8V faulty bit 3 on = +12V faulty bit 4 on = -12V faulty.

gnAgnLogFileLineBERCur.name: gnAgnLogFileLineBERCur
gnAgnLogFileLineBERCur.description: This is the Line BER (Bit Error Rate), during the alarm acceptance. Included for future development, not currently supported.

gnAgnLogFileRadioBERCur.name: gnAgnLogFileRadioBERCur
gnAgnLogFileRadioBERCur.description: This is the Radio BER (Bit Error Rate), during the alarm acceptance. Included for future development, not currently supported.

gnAgnNTPCfgSummerAdjOffset.name: gnAgnNTPCfgSummerAdjOffset
gnAgnNTPCfgSummerAdjOffset.description: The summer adjustment offset (minutes). Possible values: -1439..1439.

gnAgnNTPCfgSummerAdjStart.name: gnAgnNTPCfgSummerAdjStart
gnAgnNTPCfgSummerAdjStart.description: The summertime adjustment start. In order to set this value: 1.Turn every parameter (month, day, hour, minute) to hexadecimal. 2.Write them all together - from left to right. 3.Turn the accepted number to decimal basis. For example: in order to set 11:27:1:55 --> 11 = 0x0b, 27 = 0x1b, 1 = 0x01, 55 = 0x37 --> the 4 parameters together: 0x0b1b0137 = 186319159 (the last number is the one to set).

gnAgnNTPCfgSummerAdjEnd.name: gnAgnNTPCfgSummerAdjEnd
gnAgnNTPCfgSummerAdjEnd.description: The summertime adjustment end. In order to set this value: 1.Turn every parameter (month, day, hour, minute) to hexadecimal. 2.Write them all together - from left to right. 3.Turn the accepted number to decimal basis. For example: in order to set 11:27:1:55 --> 11 = 0x0b, 27 = 0x1b, 1 = 0x01, 55 = 0x37 --> the 4 parameters together: 0x0b1b0137 = 186319159 (the last number is the one to set).

gnAgnInBandMngNetworkElementType.description: The element type of a single unit on the inband network (Gateway or Network Element).

gnAgnInBandMngRadioChannel.name: gnAgnInBandMngRadioChannel
gnAgnInBandMngRadioChannel.description: The channel the in-band-management goes over (DCCR\DCCM\etc.).

gnAgnInBandMngUnknownPackets.name: gnAgnInBandMngUnknownPackets
gnAgnInBandMngUnknownPackets.description: Select if unknown packets will be transparently transmitted over the RING or discarded and dropped.

gnAgnInBandMngRingIpSubnet.name: gnAgnInBandMngRingIpSubnet
gnAgnInBandMngRingIpSubnet.description: The IP subnet address of the ring.

gnAgnInBandMngRingIpMask.name: gnAgnInBandMngRingIpMask
gnAgnInBandMngRingIpMask.description: The IP mask of the ring subnet address.

gnAgnInBandMngNetworkId.name: gnAgnInBandMngNetworkId
gnAgnInBandMngNetworkId.description: Identification for single link path of PPPoE over cross-networks.

gnAgnInBandMngLineMode.name: gnAgnInBandMngLineMode
gnAgnInBandMngLineMode.description: Enable the user to force PPPoE mode instead of DCCR line communication.

gnAgnInBandMngXChannelTable.name: gnAgnInBandMngXChannelTable
gnAgnInBandMngXChannelTable.description: This table defines the inband channels mapping.

gnAgnInBandMngXChannelEntry.name: gnAgnInBandMngXChannelEntry
gnAgnInBandMngXChannelEntry.description: This is an entry in the inband channel table. This table contains a row for every channel (1..4). First 3 physical channels are available in the 8 possible mapping options (on both carrier drawers). An additional channel (4) is available on the IDC (PPPoE)).

gnAgnInBandMngXChannelIfIndex.name: gnAgnInBandMngXChannelIfIndex
gnAgnInBandMngXChannelIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface that is mapped to this channel

gnAgnInBandMngXChannelType.name: gnAgnInBandMngXChannelType
gnAgnInBandMngXChannelType.description: The type of channel the in-band-management goes over. Default value for channels 1 and 3 in the carrier drawers is Proprietary. Channel 2 not allowed to be Proprietary. In protection the ch_type of ch#3 can not be modified Channel 4 must be PPPoE

gnAgnInBandMngXChannelNeighborIP.name: gnAgnInBandMngXChannelNeighborIP
gnAgnInBandMngXChannelNeighborIP.description: The PPP IP address of the gateway network element.

gnAgnInBandMngXChannelStatus.name: gnAgnInBandMngXChannelStatus
gnAgnInBandMngXChannelStatus.description: This MIB parameter defines the In-band PPP connection status. If the MIB value is up the PPP connection is up and running If the MIB value is down the PPP connection is down and is in initialization state. (Trying to establish a connection) If the MIB value is closed the PPP connection is down and is not trying open a connection.

gnAgnInBandMngXEnableInbandChannels.name: gnAgnInBandMngXEnableInbandChannels
gnAgnInBandMngXEnableInbandChannels.description: This configuration enables/disables the in-band channels: 1-4. The LSB represent channel 1, the 2nd bit channel 2, etc. If a bit is on (1) it's channel is enabled. Example: if channels 2 & 4 are enabled and channels 1 & 3 are disabled, then the binary value is 1010, so the MIB value (decimal integer) will be 10.

gnAgnInBandMngMainGNEInterface.name: gnAgnInBandMngMainGNEInterface
gnAgnInBandMngMainGNEInterface.description: determines the primary GNE channel. Default means fixed channel prioritizing, in the following order (from first to last): Right Carrier Radio interface, [STM-1] Line interface on either Left or Right Carrier, Left Carrier Radio interface and PPPoE interface.

gnNeighborInBandTable.name: gnNeighborInBandTable
gnNeighborInBandTable.description: This table defines the IP addresses of the units that are connected Inband.

gnNeighborInBandEntry.description: This is an entry in the IP addresses of the units that are connected Inband. This table contains a row for every interface which type is logically connected. for example regenerator which is connected in band has two neighbors: the first (index 1) the remote radio unit and the second the remote fiber neighbor (index 2).

gnNeighborInBandIP.name: gnNeighborInBandIP
gnNeighborInBandIP.description: The PPP IP address of the gateway network element.

gnNeighborInBandStatus.name: gnNeighborInBandStatus
gnNeighborInBandStatus.description: This MIB parameter defines the In-band PPP connection status. If the MIB value is up the PPP connection is up and running If the MIB value is down the PPP connection is down and is in initialization state. (Trying to establish a connection) If the MIB value is closed the PPP connection is down and is not trying open a connection.

gnNeighborRemoteRadioIP.name: gnNeighborRemoteRadioIP
gnNeighborRemoteRadioIP.description: The IP address of the Radio Remote IDU.

gnNeighborInBandXTable.name: gnNeighborInBandXTable
gnNeighborInBandXTable.description: This table defines the IP addresses of the units that are connected Inband.

gnNeighborInBandXEntry.name: gnNeighborInBandXEntry
gnNeighborInBandXEntry.description: This is an entry in the IP addresses of the units that are connected Inband. This table contains a row for every interface which type is logically connected. for example regenerator which is connected in band has two neighbors: the first (index 1) the remote radio unit and the second the remote fiber neighbor (index 2).

gnNeighborInBandXIP.name: gnNeighborInBandXIP
gnNeighborInBandXIP.description: The PPP IP address of the gateway network element.

gnNeighborIpTable.name: gnNeighborIpTable
gnNeighborIpTable.description: This table shows the Neighbor IP for each STM connection.

gnNeighborIpDetectMode.name: gnNeighborIpDetectMode
gnNeighborIpDetectMode.description: The Neighbor detect can be done automatically or to be manually insreted. Disable marks that the IP Detect is not used.

gnNeighborIpRemoteIfIndex.name: gnNeighborIpRemoteIfIndex
gnNeighborIpRemoteIfIndex.description: The If index of the neighbor IP address connected to the current If Index.

gnSoftwareDrawerVersionTable.name: gnSoftwareDrawerVersionTable
gnSoftwareDrawerVersionTable.description: This table contains the IDU, MUX & ODU software versions; local and remote.

gnSoftwareDrawerVersionEntry.name: gnSoftwareDrawerVersionEntry
gnSoftwareDrawerVersionEntry.description: Entry containing the currently operating IDU, ODU and MUX software versions.

gnSoftwareDrawerId.name: gnSoftwareDrawerId
gnSoftwareDrawerId.description: The ID indicates which Drawer is involved in the specific row.

gnSoftwareDrawerVersionMUX.name: gnSoftwareDrawerVersionMUX
gnSoftwareDrawerVersionMUX.description: This is the MUX software version.

gnSoftwareDrawerVersionMUXPostResetVersi.name: gnSoftwareDrawerVersionMUXPostResetVersion
gnSoftwareDrawerVersionMUXPostResetVersi.description: This is the ODU software version.

gnSoftwareDrawerVersionODU.name: gnSoftwareDrawerVersionODU
gnSoftwareDrawerVersionODU.description: This is the MUX post reset software version.

gnSoftwareDrawerVersionODUPostResetVersi.name: gnSoftwareDrawerVersionODUPostResetVersion
gnSoftwareDrawerVersionODUPostResetVersi.description: This is the MUX post reset software version.

gnSoftwareDrawerVersionModemFile.name: gnSoftwareDrawerVersionModemFile
gnSoftwareDrawerVersionModemFile.description: This is the Modem software version.

gnSoftwareDrawerVersionModemFilePostRese.name: gnSoftwareDrawerVersionModemFilePostResetVersion
gnSoftwareDrawerVersionModemFilePostRese.description: This is the Modem post reset software version.

gnSoftwareDrawerVersionModemScript.name: gnSoftwareDrawerVersionModemScript
gnSoftwareDrawerVersionModemScript.description: This is the Modem software version.

gnSoftwareDrawerVersionModemScriptPostRe.name: gnSoftwareDrawerVersionModemScriptPostResetVersion
gnSoftwareDrawerVersionModemScriptPostRe.description: This is the Modem post reset software version.

gnSoftwareDrawerVersionRfuFpgaVersion.name: gnSoftwareDrawerVersionRfuFpgaVersion
gnSoftwareDrawerVersionRfuFpgaVersion.description: This is the Rfu Fpga software version.

gnAgnCurrentAlarmLastChange.name: gnAgnCurrentAlarmLastChange
gnAgnCurrentAlarmLastChange.description: This counter initialized with random number after resest, and incremented on each change in the gnAgnCurrentAlarmTable (either add or remove of an entery).

gnAgnCurrentAlarmTable.name: gnAgnCurrentAlarmTable
gnAgnCurrentAlarmTable.description: This table includes the currently open alarm (when a RAISED trap is sent, an alarm is added to the table, when a CLEAR trap is sent, the alarm is removed.

gnAgnCurrentAlarmEntry.name: gnAgnCurrentAlarmEntry
gnAgnCurrentAlarmEntry.description: Entry containing the info of a currently RAISED trap.

gnAgnCurrentAlarmCounter.name: gnAgnCurrentAlarmCounter
gnAgnCurrentAlarmCounter.description: A running counter of open alarm, the counter is incremented on every new RAISED trap. It is cleared after reset. This counter is (optionaly) attached to each trap.

gnAgnCurrentAlarmId.name: gnAgnCurrentAlarmId
gnAgnCurrentAlarmId.description: Alarm Identifier (contains alarm type and interface). Same AlarmId for rasie and clear alarms.

gnAgnCurrentAlarmIfIndex.name: gnAgnCurrentAlarmIfIndex
gnAgnCurrentAlarmIfIndex.description: Interface Index where the alarm occurred, alarms that are not associated with specific interface will have the following value: For IDC related alarms the value is: 65001 For drawer1 related alarms the value is: 65003 For drawer2 related alarms the value is: 65004 If Alarm's origin is bigger than 256, it will be 65000 + the origin

gnAgnCurrentAlarmOrigin.name: gnAgnCurrentAlarmOrigin
gnAgnCurrentAlarmOrigin.description: The origin drawer of the alarm (if applicable, otherwise it will be idc(2)).

gnAgnCurrentAlarmTrapID.name: gnAgnCurrentAlarmTrapID
gnAgnCurrentAlarmTrapID.description: The ID of the RAISED trap that was sent when this alarm was raised.

gnAgnCurrentAlarmTimeT.name: gnAgnCurrentAlarmTimeT
gnAgnCurrentAlarmTimeT.description: Timestamp of this alarm, this number is the seconds from midnight 1.1.1970.

gnAgnCurrentAlarmText.name: gnAgnCurrentAlarmText
gnAgnCurrentAlarmText.description: The alarm display text (same as the text in the sent trap).

gnApplicFileTable.name: gnApplicFileTable
gnApplicFileTable.description: This table contains the application file list.

gnApplicFileEntry.name: gnApplicFileEntry
gnApplicFileEntry.description: Entry containing the application file list.

gnApplicFileId.name: gnApplicFileId
gnApplicFileId.description: The ID indicates which device is involved in the specific row. The application file table includes two rows, one for the local radio and one for the remote radio.

gnApplicFileName.name: gnApplicFileName
gnApplicFileName.description: This is the application file name.

gnApplicFileVersion.name: gnApplicFileVersion
gnApplicFileVersion.description: This is the application file version.

gnApplicFileCreateDate.name: gnApplicFileCreateDate
gnApplicFileCreateDate.description: This parameter specifies the application file download date Format 'YYYY-MM-DD,HH:MM:SS' (Hexadecimal). A date-time specification. field octets contents range ----- ------ -------- ----- 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) 7 8 deci-seconds 0..9 8 9 direction from UTC '+' / '-' 9 10 hours from UTC 0..11 10 11 minutes from UTC 0..59 For example, Tuesday May 26, 1992 at 1:30:15 PM EDT would be displayed as: 07 c8 05 1a 0d 1e 0f 00 ( 1992 -5 -26,13:30:15 ) Note that if only local time is known, then timezone information (fields 8-10) is not present.

gnApplicFileDownloadDate.name: gnApplicFileDownloadDate
gnApplicFileDownloadDate.description: This parameter specifies the application file download date Format 'YYYY-MM-DD,HH:MM:SS' (Hexadecimal). A date-time specification. field octets contents range ----- ------ -------- ----- 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) 7 8 deci-seconds 0..9 8 9 direction from UTC '+' / '-' 9 10 hours from UTC 0..11 10 11 minutes from UTC 0..59 For example, Tuesday May 26, 1992 at 1:30:15 PM EDT would be displayed as: 07 c8 05 1a 0d 1e 0f 00 ( 1992 -5 -26,13:30:15 ) Note that if only local time is known, then timezone information (fields 8-10) is not present.

gnApplicFileType.name: gnApplicFileType
gnApplicFileType.description: This is the application file type.

gnApplicFileSubType.name: gnApplicFileSubType
gnApplicFileSubType.description: This is the application file sub type.

gnApplicFileFirmware.name: gnApplicFileFirmware
gnApplicFileFirmware.description: This is the application file firmware.

gnApplicFileGeneralPurpose.name: gnApplicFileGeneralPurpose
gnApplicFileGeneralPurpose.description: This is the application file General Purpose.

gnApplicFileSize.name: gnApplicFileSize
gnApplicFileSize.description: This is the application file size in bytes.

gnApplicFileCompressed.name: gnApplicFileCompressed
gnApplicFileCompressed.description: This is indicate the application file compress status.

gnApplicFileDssSupport.name: gnApplicFileDssSupport
gnApplicFileDssSupport.description: This is indicate the application file DSS support.

gnApplicFileCrcSupport.name: gnApplicFileCrcSupport
gnApplicFileCrcSupport.description: This is indicate the application file CRC support.

gnDiskUsedspace.name: gnDiskUsedspace
gnDiskUsedspace.description: The ID indicates Disk Used space.

gnDiskFreespace.name: gnDiskFreespace
gnDiskFreespace.description: The ID indicates Disk Free space.

gnOduCfgTable.name: gnOduCfgTable
gnOduCfgTable.description: This table defines the configuration of the Outdoor part of the system.

gnOduCfgEntry.name: gnOduCfgEntry
gnOduCfgEntry.description: This is an entry in the ODU Configuration Table. This table contains two rows, indexed by ifIndex= 1 for local ODU and ifIndex = 101 for remote ODU.

gnOduCfgTransmitterFrequency.name: gnOduCfgTransmitterFrequency
gnOduCfgTransmitterFrequency.description: This parameter indicates the radio TX channel number. WRITE will change the LOCAL side only. Not all radios will support TX frequency change via channel numbers.

gnOduCfgRLPerfMonThresh1.name: gnOduCfgRLPerfMonThresh1
gnOduCfgRLPerfMonThresh1.description: When the Received Level (RL) exceeds this threshold a performance monitoring RL1 counter increments.

gnOduCfgRLPerfMonThresh2.name: gnOduCfgRLPerfMonThresh2
gnOduCfgRLPerfMonThresh2.description: When the Received Level (RL) exceeds this threshold a performance monitoring RL2 counter increments.

gnOduCfgATPCStatus.name: gnOduCfgATPCStatus
gnOduCfgATPCStatus.description: This parameter indicates if the ATPC option is enabled or disabled.

gnOduCfgMUTEStatus.name: gnOduCfgMUTEStatus
gnOduCfgMUTEStatus.description: This parameter indicates if transmitter will be in mute state. (Mute on -> don't transmit)

gnOduCfgAntennaType.name: gnOduCfgAntennaType
gnOduCfgAntennaType.description: This parameter indicates the size of the antenna used in the ODU. This attribute will not auto-detect the antenna size. It is used for the unfaded RSL calculation feature included in the element manager.

gnOduCfgTransmitLevel.name: gnOduCfgTransmitLevel
gnOduCfgTransmitLevel.description: This is the transmitter output power level of the signal transmitted by the radios, displayed in DBM.

gnOduCfgRealTxFreqNumber.name: gnOduCfgRealTxFreqNumber
gnOduCfgRealTxFreqNumber.description: Identifies the RF Tx frequency. For 6, 7 and 8 bands the Tx frequency resolution is in kHz, for other bands the resolution is in 10kHz. If the Tx frequency value is over 4000000 than the band is identified as 6, 7 or 8G band.

gnOduCfgRealRxFreqNumber.name: gnOduCfgRealRxFreqNumber
gnOduCfgRealRxFreqNumber.description: Identifies the RF Rx frequency. For 6, 7 and 8 bands the Rx frequency resolution is in kHz, for other bands the resolution is in 10kHz. If the Rx frequency value is over 4000000 than the band is identified as 6, 7 or 8G band.

gnOduCfgMinTxFreqNumber.name: gnOduCfgMinTxFreqNumber
gnOduCfgMinTxFreqNumber.description: This the Minimum TX frequency that the ODU can receive - Used by the management station.

gnOduCfgMaxTxFreqNumber.name: gnOduCfgMaxTxFreqNumber
gnOduCfgMaxTxFreqNumber.description: This the Maximum TX frequency that the ODU can receive - Used by the management station.

gnOduCfgMaxTxLevel.name: gnOduCfgMaxTxLevel
gnOduCfgMaxTxLevel.description: This is the theoretical maximum level that this ODU unit can transmit.

gnOduCfgRefRsl.name: gnOduCfgRefRsl
gnOduCfgRefRsl.description: This is the received level reference, applicable when utilizing ATPC mode; displayed in dBm.

gnOduCfgForceRmtMuteTx.name: gnOduCfgForceRmtMuteTx
gnOduCfgForceRmtMuteTx.description: When on, this parameter force the transmitter to be in mute state. (Mute on -> don't transmit)

gnOduCfgForceRmtMaxTx.name: gnOduCfgForceRmtMaxTx
gnOduCfgForceRmtMaxTx.description: This parameter force the transmitter output power level of the signal transmitted by the radio.

gnOduCfgTLPerfMonThresh1.name: gnOduCfgTLPerfMonThresh1
gnOduCfgTLPerfMonThresh1.description: When the Transmitted Level (TL) exceeds this threshold a performance monitoring TL1 counter increments.

gnOduCfgMinRxFreqNumber.name: gnOduCfgMinRxFreqNumber
gnOduCfgMinRxFreqNumber.description: This the Minimum RX frequency that the ODU can receive - Used by the management station.

gnOduCfgMaxRxFreqNumber.name: gnOduCfgMaxRxFreqNumber
gnOduCfgMaxRxFreqNumber.description: This the Maximum RX frequency that the ODU can receive - Used by the management station.

gnOduCfgOduLoopSupport.name: gnOduCfgOduLoopSupport
gnOduCfgOduLoopSupport.description: Indication for loopback support by the connected ODU.

gnOduCfgFreqDevider.name: gnOduCfgFreqDevider
gnOduCfgFreqDevider.description: Indicates the number with which we should divide the MIB Freq value to get to the actual Freq (100 or 1000)

gnOduStatusTable.name: gnOduStatusTable
gnOduStatusTable.description: This table defines the status of the Outdoor unit of the system.

gnOduStatusEntry.name: gnOduStatusEntry
gnOduStatusEntry.description: This is an entry in the ODU Status Table. This table contains two rows, indexed by ifIndex= 1 for local ODU and ifIndex = 101 for remote ODU.

gnOduStatusCelsiusTemp.name: gnOduStatusCelsiusTemp
gnOduStatusCelsiusTemp.description: This is the temperature of the ODU in degrees Celsius.

gnOduStatusFahrenheitTemp.name: gnOduStatusFahrenheitTemp
gnOduStatusFahrenheitTemp.description: This is the temperature of the ODU in degrees Fahrenheit.

gnOduStatusTransmitLevel.name: gnOduStatusTransmitLevel
gnOduStatusTransmitLevel.description: This is the transmit level of the signal transmitted by the radios transmitter, displayed in DBM.

gnOduStatusReceiveLevel.name: gnOduStatusReceiveLevel
gnOduStatusReceiveLevel.description: This is the receive level of the signal transmitted by the radios transmitter, displayed in DBM.

gnOduStatusSynthesizerVCOLock.name: gnOduStatusSynthesizerVCOLock
gnOduStatusSynthesizerVCOLock.description: This octet represents the ODU status as follows (bit 1, LSB): bit 1 on = TX IF synthesizer bit 2 on = RX IF synthesizer bit 3 on = Xband synthesizer bit 4 on = History TX IF synthesizer bit 5 on = History RX IF synthesizer bit 6 on = History Xband synthesizer

gnOduStatusPowerSupply.name: gnOduStatusPowerSupply
gnOduStatusPowerSupply.description: This octet represents the status of the power supplies of the ODU: bit 1 on = +5V faulty bit 2 on = +8V faulty bit 3 on = +12V faulty bit 4 on = -12V faulty.

gnOduStatusClearLoopTimer.name: gnOduStatusClearLoopTimer
gnOduStatusClearLoopTimer.description: This variable indicates the remaining time (in minutes) till the relevant odu loopback timer will be expired. when starting a loopback and the value of gnGenCfgClearLoopTimeout is x, the gnOduStatusClearLoopTimer will be also x, after one minute it will be x-1, etc.

gnOduMonCurrTable.name: gnOduMonCurrTable
gnOduMonCurrTable.description: This table defines/keeps the counters of the current 15 min interval.

gnOduMonCurrEntry.name: gnOduMonCurrEntry
gnOduMonCurrEntry.description: This is an entry in the Current Interval Table. This table contains two rows, indexed by ifIndex= 1 for local ODU and ifIndex = 101 for remote ODU.

gnOduMonCurrMinRL.name: gnOduMonCurrMinRL
gnOduMonCurrMinRL.description: The minimum received signal level (RL) in the current 15 minute interval. (in DBM)

gnOduMonCurrMaxRL.name: gnOduMonCurrMaxRL
gnOduMonCurrMaxRL.description: The maximum received signal level (RL) in the current 15 minute interval. (in DBM).

gnOduMonCurrTLThresh1Exceed.name: gnOduMonCurrTLThresh1Exceed
gnOduMonCurrTLThresh1Exceed.description: The number of seconds TL exceeded the TL1 threshold in the last 15 minutes.

gnOduMonCurrRLThresh1Exceed.name: gnOduMonCurrRLThresh1Exceed
gnOduMonCurrRLThresh1Exceed.description: The number of seconds RL exceeded the RL1 threshold in the last 15 minutes.

gnOduMonCurrRLThresh2Exceed.name: gnOduMonCurrRLThresh2Exceed
gnOduMonCurrRLThresh2Exceed.description: The number of seconds RL exceeded the RL2 threshold in the last 15 minutes.

gnOduMonCurrDayMinRL.name: gnOduMonCurrDayMinRL
gnOduMonCurrDayMinRL.description: The minimum Receive Level (in DBM). in the last 24 hours.

gnOduMonCurrDayMaxRL.name: gnOduMonCurrDayMaxRL
gnOduMonCurrDayMaxRL.description: The maximum Receive Level (in DBM). in the last 24 hours.

gnOduMonCurrDayTLThresh1Exceed.name: gnOduMonCurrDayTLThresh1Exceed
gnOduMonCurrDayTLThresh1Exceed.description: The number of seconds TL exceeded the TL1 threshold in the last 24 hours.

gnOduMonCurrDayRLThresh1Exceed.name: gnOduMonCurrDayRLThresh1Exceed
gnOduMonCurrDayRLThresh1Exceed.description: The number of seconds RL exceeded the RL1 threshold in the last 24 hours.

gnOduMonCurrDayRLThresh2Exceed.name: gnOduMonCurrDayRLThresh2Exceed
gnOduMonCurrDayRLThresh2Exceed.description: The number of seconds RL exceeded the RL2 threshold in the last 24 hours.

gnOduMonCurrMinTL.name: gnOduMonCurrMinTL
gnOduMonCurrMinTL.description: The minimum transmitted signal level (TL) in the current 15 minute interval. (in DBM)

gnOduMonCurrMaxTL.name: gnOduMonCurrMaxTL
gnOduMonCurrMaxTL.description: The maximum transmitted signal level (TL) in the current 15 minute interval. (in DBM).

gnOduMonCurrDayMinTL.name: gnOduMonCurrDayMinTL
gnOduMonCurrDayMinTL.description: The minimum Transmitted Level (in DBM). in the last 24 hours.

gnOduMonCurrDayMaxTL.name: gnOduMonCurrDayMaxTL
gnOduMonCurrDayMaxTL.description: The maximum Transmitted Level (in DBM). in the last 24 hours.

gnOduMonIntervalTable.name: gnOduMonIntervalTable
gnOduMonIntervalTable.description: This table defines/keeps the counters of the 96 last intervals of 15 min.

gnOduMonIntervalEntry.name: gnOduMonIntervalEntry
gnOduMonIntervalEntry.description: This is an entry in the Interval Table. This table is indexed by ifIndex= 1 for local ODU and ifIndex = 101 for remote ODU and by interval idx

gnOduMonIntervalIdx.name: gnOduMonIntervalIdx
gnOduMonIntervalIdx.description: The interval number to which this row is related.

gnOduMonIntervalMinRL.name: gnOduMonIntervalMinRL
gnOduMonIntervalMinRL.description: The minimum RL in a 15 minutes interval. (in DBM).

gnOduMonIntervalMaxRL.name: gnOduMonIntervalMaxRL
gnOduMonIntervalMaxRL.description: The maximum RL in a 15 minutes interval. (in DBM).

gnOduMonIntervalTLThresh1Exceed.name: gnOduMonIntervalTLThresh1Exceed
gnOduMonIntervalTLThresh1Exceed.description: The number of seconds TL exceeded the TL1 threshold in a 15 minutes interval.

gnOduMonIntervalEvent.name: gnOduMonIntervalEvent
gnOduMonIntervalEvent.description: Events bit 1 = CommDisc. bit 2 = CommCon bit 3 = ATPC2Max. bit 4 = ATPC2Norm. Included for future development, not currently supported.

gnOduMonIntervalRLThresh1Exceed.name: gnOduMonIntervalRLThresh1Exceed
gnOduMonIntervalRLThresh1Exceed.description: The number of seconds RL exceeded the RL1 threshold in a 15 minutes interval.

gnOduMonIntervalRLThresh2Exceed.name: gnOduMonIntervalRLThresh2Exceed
gnOduMonIntervalRLThresh2Exceed.description: The number of seconds RL exceeded the RL2 threshold in a 15 minutes interval.

gnOduMonIntervalMinTL.name: gnOduMonIntervalMinTL
gnOduMonIntervalMinTL.description: The minimum TL in a 15 minutes interval. (in DBM).

gnOduMonIntervalMaxTL.name: gnOduMonIntervalMaxTL
gnOduMonIntervalMaxTL.description: The maximum TL in a 15 minutes interval. (in DBM).

gnOduMonDayTable.name: gnOduMonDayTable
gnOduMonDayTable.description: This table defines/keeps the counters of 96 intervals of 15 min.

gnOduMonDayEntry.name: gnOduMonDayEntry
gnOduMonDayEntry.description: This is an entry in the Days Table. This table is indexed by ifIndex= 1 for local ODU and ifIndex = 101 for remote ODU and by day idx. gnOduMonDayIdx = 1 is one day from now, gnOduMonDayIdx = 2 is two days from now, and so on...

gnOduMonDayIdx.name: gnOduMonDayIdx
gnOduMonDayIdx.description: The interval number to which this row is related.

gnOduMonDayMinRL.name: gnOduMonDayMinRL
gnOduMonDayMinRL.description: The minimum Receive Level (in DBM). in a 24 hour interval.

gnOduMonDayMaxRL.name: gnOduMonDayMaxRL
gnOduMonDayMaxRL.description: The maximum Receive Level (in DBM). in a 24 hour interval.

gnOduMonDayTLThresh1Exceed.name: gnOduMonDayTLThresh1Exceed
gnOduMonDayTLThresh1Exceed.description: The number of seconds TL exceeded the TL1 threshold in a 24 hour interval.

gnOduMonDayRLThresh1Exceed.name: gnOduMonDayRLThresh1Exceed
gnOduMonDayRLThresh1Exceed.description: The number of seconds RL exceeded the RL1 threshold in a 24 hour interval.

gnOduMonDayRLThresh2Exceed.name: gnOduMonDayRLThresh2Exceed
gnOduMonDayRLThresh2Exceed.description: The number of seconds RL exceeded the RL2 threshold in a 24 hour interval.

gnOduMonDayMinTL.name: gnOduMonDayMinTL
gnOduMonDayMinTL.description: The minimum Transmit Level (in DBM). in a 24 hour interval.

gnOduMonDayMaxTL.name: gnOduMonDayMaxTL
gnOduMonDayMaxTL.description: The maximum Transmit Level (in DBM). in a 24 hour interval.

gnOduCfgXTable.description: This table defines the configuration of the Outdoor part of the system.

gnOduCfgXEntry.name: gnOduCfgXEntry
gnOduCfgXEntry.description: This is an entry in the ODU Configuration Table. This table contains two rows, indexed by gnOduCfgXId= 3 for drawer1 ODU and gnOduCfgXId = 4 for drawer2 ODU.

gnOduCfgXTxFreqNumLocalRemote.name: gnOduCfgXTxFreqNumLocalRemote
gnOduCfgXTxFreqNumLocalRemote.description: Indicates the radio transmit frequency, displayed in 1/100 MHz. WRITE changes the local and remote sides. Only for systems that support frequency configuration (Not channel).

gnOduCfgXRLPerfMonThresh1.name: gnOduCfgXRLPerfMonThresh1
gnOduCfgXRLPerfMonThresh1.description: When the Received Level (RL) exceeds this threshold a performance monitoring RL1 counter increments.

gnHptCfgTug3Structure1.name: gnHptCfgTug3Structure1
gnHptCfgTug3Structure1.description: This field set the TUG-3 #1 structure: (hexadecimal number) the lsb 4 bits set VC12=0 or VC3=1 structure to the TUG3 #1. (the K of the KLM index is 1) for VC12 structure the next 21 bits (for SDH) or 28 bits (for SONET) set each of the VC12 to be blocked (bit is 0) or unblocked (bit is 1). if it is VC3 only one more bit indicates if it is blocked (0) or unblocked (1). if a VC12 is set to blocked (this is the default) the system will send TU-AIS in that VC12. it it is unblocked it will be path-through or mapped to a E1/T1 port (according to the gnAccessCfgLowPathIndex). the 21 or 28 bits order is as folwed (from lsb to msb direction): first 7 bits for M=1 (from KLM index), the next 7 bits for M=2, the next for M=3, and the last (only for SONET) for M=4. Example : SDH, VC12 strcture, blocked VCs: KLM=111,121 (M=1), 112,122 (M=2), 163,173 (M=3), unblocked VCs: all the other. the value in bits will be: 0011111 1111100 1111100 0000, and in Hexadecimal: 0x7FE7C0. (so enter: 00 7F E7 C0).

gnEthStatisticAFrameReceivedOkMsb.name: gnEthStatisticAFrameReceivedOkMsb

gnEthStatisticCRCAlignErrorsMsb.description: The total number of packets received that had a length (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) of between 64 and 1518 octets, inclusive, but had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error), (MSB).
